abstract: The conviction of Mr. Skelos and his son, Adam, in a retrial was the fourth major Albany corruption case won by federal prosecutors in the last five months.
snippet: The conviction of Mr. Skelos and his son, Adam, in a retrial was the fourth major Albany corruption case won by federal prosecutors in the last five months.
lead_paragraph: Dean G. Skelos, once one of the most powerful figures in New York State politics, was found guilty of bribery, extortion and conspiracy on Tuesday, the latest in a drumbeat of corruption convictions to roil Albany in a heated election year.

abstract: The indictment of 12 Russian operatives provides never-before-seen detail about the central role of the online avatar Guccifer 2.0 in the dissemination of stolen Democratic documents.
snippet: The indictment of 12 Russian operatives provides never-before-seen detail about the central role of the online avatar Guccifer 2.0 in the dissemination of stolen Democratic documents.
lead_paragraph: The message from WikiLeaks in July 2016 to a group of Russian intelligence officers who prosecutors say were posing as a Romanian hacker named Guccifer 2.0 urged swift action before the opening of the Democratic National Convention that month.

abstract: All of the weddings right here on one handy page for you.
snippet: All of the weddings right here on one handy page for you.
lead_paragraph: Lauren Wright was a new Ph.D. student in American government at Georgetown in the fall of 2011. She was instantly attracted to Jonathan Mummolo, a second-year Ph.D. student with casual good looks in jeans and rolled-up shirt sleeves, intently leading an orientation meeting.

abstract: Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo said he was powerless to “stop people from doing criminal things,” saying the problem lay in human nature, not his administration.
snippet: Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo said he was powerless to “stop people from doing criminal things,” saying the problem lay in human nature, not his administration.
lead_paragraph: ALBANY — The conviction of Alain E. Kaloyeros, Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo’s economic development guru, on federal corruption charges on Thursday has provided a timely and powerful cudgel to a raft of critics and political opponents running to replace him.

abstract: A by-no-means exhaustive list of the things our editors (and a few contributors) find interesting on a given week.
snippet: A by-no-means exhaustive list of the things our editors (and a few contributors) find interesting on a given week.
lead_paragraph: About a decade ago, the Swedish designer Fredrik Paulsen began creating furniture from pine stained with impressionistic swaths of brilliant color, resembling a summer horizon on fire. The technique was labor intensive to the point that he began to think of himself as “the anti-Ikea" because of the time it took to produce a single unique piece.

headline_main: Rainbow Furniture, Nighties and More Things T Editors Like Right Now

abstract: Recent concert stagings of “West Side Story” and “On the Town” show the pitfalls — and solutions — for symphonic performances of these musicals.
snippet: Recent concert stagings of “West Side Story” and “On the Town” show the pitfalls — and solutions — for symphonic performances of these musicals.
lead_paragraph: When I first fell in love with “West Side Story,” as a teenager, I tried to find as many cast recordings as I could. The Broadway original was energetic and earnest; the film soundtrack was lush and familiar. But what a shock it was to find that the worst album out there was the one conducted by Leonard Bernstein himself.

abstract: President Trump again denounced Mr. Khan’s record on crime and terrorism. It seemed more of a personal attack than a policy point.
snippet: President Trump again denounced Mr. Khan’s record on crime and terrorism. It seemed more of a personal attack than a policy point.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — President Trump opened the second stage of his European tour, in Britain, with a blistering attack on two of his favorite targets, Prime Minister Theresa May and the mayor of London, Sadiq Khan, even before he touched down in the country.

abstract: He’s a ‘diva.’ He ‘doesn’t have a post game.’ And he’s ‘really cocky.’ The Lakers’ newest star has not been embraced by many Kobe devotees.
snippet: He’s a ‘diva.’ He ‘doesn’t have a post game.’ And he’s ‘really cocky.’ The Lakers’ newest star has not been embraced by many Kobe devotees.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — The Los Angeles Lakers recently acquired a high-profile player, but many longtime fans have been arriving here for N.B.A. Summer League paying homage to the past. They wear jerseys bearing the Nos. 8 and 24, which belonged to Kobe Bryant during his long and productive career and now hang from the rafters in Staples Center.

abstract: A federal judge approved the deal a month ago, saying the federal agency did not sufficiently prove that the merger would harm competition and consumers.
snippet: A federal judge approved the deal a month ago, saying the federal agency did not sufficiently prove that the merger would harm competition and consumers.
lead_paragraph: The federal government on Thursday mounted a new effort to unravel AT&T’s deal with Time Warner, a blockbuster merger that has already started to reshape the media industry.
